Laboratory tests have confirmed 31 additional cases of meningitis, an acute inflammation of the brain and spinal cord, in some areas of the central state of Niger. In 2017, Nigeria declared that the outbreak of meningitis in the country is over, but only after it killed 1 166 people, most', of' them children. Vaccination campaigns were carried out in Zamfara, Sokoto, Yobe and Katsina states, the worst affected by the outbreak. A new strain of meningitis C was first reported in Zamfara in November 2016 and spread to 22 other states in northern Nigeria.

--SABC--

